must
confess
that
the
nature
of
her
complaint
alarmed
him
considerably."
And
in
this
style
he
talked
on
for
some
time
very
properly,
not
much
attending
to
any
answer,
but
altogether
sufficiently
awake
to
the
terror
of
a
bad
sore
throat;
and
Emma
was
quite
in
charity
with
him.
But
at
last
there
seemed
a
perverse
turn;
it
seemed
all
at
once
as
