to
avoid
the
danger
of
catching
an
ulcerated
sore
throat
herself.
Is
this
fair,
Mrs.
Weston?
Judge
between
us.
Have
not
I
some
right
to
complain?
I
am
sure
of
your
kind
support
and
aid."
Emma
saw
Mrs.
Weston's
surprize,
and
felt
that
it
must
be
great,
at
an
address
which,
in
words
and
